It seems pyright or vim respects the `PYENV_VERSION` environment variable.
Running nvim with `PYENV_VERSION=myvirtualenvname nvim`  makes nvim pick up the correct virtual environment. You can also execute this command: `pyenv shell <myvirtualenvname>`

@jzelinskie describes well what is going on: https://github.com/microsoft/pyright/issues/1456#issuecomment-774636220
